1. rei publicae: dat. of indirect object (ξ 16).

2. bene dicere: as the literary works of the ancients were primarily intended to be read aloud, dicere is habitually used as a synonym of scribere. The context also shows that bene dicere cannot refer to oratorical excel- lence here, for that would not be a contrast to benefacere, as the states- man and the orator in antiquity were generally combined in one man.
